Dashboard 1: Customer Support Performance Overview


-->This dashboard provides a high level operational overview of customer support activities.

-->Displays total tickets, average response time, and first response metrics.

-->Shows ticket priority and communication channel distribution.

-->Identifies top products generating support requests.

-->Analyzes customer demographics including gender and age groups.

-->Tracks response time trends to evaluate team performance.

Purpose:
To answer — Who is raising tickets, how urgent they are, and where support effort is concentrated.


 Dashboard 2: Issue Analysis


-->This dashboard focuses on deeper investigation of support issues and patterns.

-->Highlights total high-priority tickets and tickets per customer.

-->Tracks ticket trends across months and years.

-->Compares ticket subjects across priority levels.

-->Analyzes ticket types across different purchased products.

Purpose:
To answer — Why issues occur and which products or problems require immediate action.



  DAX functions used:
1. Avg First Response Time (hrs) = 
AVERAGEX(
    Fact_Tickets,
    Fact_Tickets[First Response Time] / 3600
)


2.Avg ResponseTime (hrs) = 
AVERAGEX(Fact_Tickets,Fact_Tickets[Response Time Fixed (hrs)]/3600)

3.Total Tickets = 
COUNT ( Fact_Tickets[Ticket ID] )

4.Tickets per Customer = 
DIVIDE(
    [Total Tickets],
    DISTINCTCOUNT('Fact_Tickets'[Customer_Key])
)

5.High Priority Tickets = 
CALCULATE(
    [Total Tickets],
    'Dim_Ticket'[Ticket Priority] = "High"
)
  
